tickets.description:
like mentioned [[https://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/58420#comment:6|here]] I'd like to know if we want to unify the different die() calls we use:

{{{#!php
// Don't load directly.
if ( ! defined( 'ABSPATH' ) ) {
	die( '-1' );
}
}}}

(mostly used, having a comment)

{{{#!php
if ( ! defined( 'ABSPATH' ) ) {
	die();
}
}}}

(**not** having a comment), like seen in **\wp-admin\link-parse-opml.php**, **\wp-admin\site-health-info.php**

or even

{{{#!php
if ( ! defined( 'ABSPATH' ) ) {
	exit();
}
}}}

like seen in **\wp-includes\rss-functions.php**
